In the meantime, four hotel projects totalling nearly 600 rooms will emerge within two years.
For Titan's CEO, "Goodyear Amiens' buying project starts with zero employees"
Maurice Taylor, CEO of the U.S. tyre manufacturer Titan, declared today that he was ready to save 333 jobs out of the 1,137 jobs in the plant after throwing the towel with a crash in January for the partial takeover of Amiens-Nord's Goodyear site.
Arnaud Montebourg, Minister for Productive Recovery, had already announced this on Monday 21 October.
